Reasoning: The paper discusses the extension of Shannon's mathematical theory of communication to include the concept of mutual redundancy in inter-human communication systems. This involves the measurement and interpretation of information in sociological cases using different meaning-processing structures. The paper touches on topics related to information theory (cs.IT), social systems (cs.SY), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cybernetics (cs.CY). However, the focus on communication and meaning processing in social systems makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) the most likely category.
